HEADWORD: Shaddock
<hw>Shad"dock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Said to be so
called from a Captain <ets>Shaddock</ets>, who first brought this fruit
from the East Indies.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tree (<spn>Citrus
decumana</spn>) and its fruit, which is a large species of orange; --
called also <altname>forbidden fruit</altname>, and
<altname>pompelmous</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shade</ent>⟦br⟧
